Watch our Instagram LIVE event 

Our partners at Curaleaf and there CSR (Corporate Social Responsibility) team joined us to have a discussion about there Rooted in Good initiative and how their supplier diversity works and how are you as a supplier/business/brand are able to participate.

This is an intro conversation to our larger virtual event on September 3, so #savethedate. There where we do a deeper dive into #420by2025 and hear from  a few of the brands that are currently participating and how it has been an asset to their brand, selection processes and more. 

#womenincannabis #rootedingood #curaleaf #womengrow

On Monday, 8/23…Let’s Talk Supplier Diversity!!

Supplier Diversity programs are ones that encourage the use of minority owned, women owned, veteran owned, LGBTQ owned businesses as suppliers. 

What does that mean in cannabis? Why is it so important to our industry?

Our partners at @curaleaf.usa and there CSR (Corporate Social Responsibility) team will be joining us to have a discussion about there Rooted in Good initiative and how their supplier diversity works and how are you as a supplier/business/brand are able to participate.

Join us for our Instagram LIVE event on August 23 at noon EST

Our next installment of G-Suite Conversations…the Women Grow podcast. 

Keep Inviting Different People to the Table: Emily Paxhia 

Gia welcomes Emily Paxhia, Co-Founder and Managing Partner of Cannabis Investment Firm @poseidon.investments 

Emily has helped to shape many pitches, presentations, and has reviewed thousands of investment questions. She talks with us about applying her education in psychology to business, and why there is nothing like being in the room and learning to speak up confidently with your own opinion. Emily shares why she decided to give cannabis a chance as an early investor in 2012 and start Poseidon with her brother Morgan, along with the important things we should know developing in the present and future within the cannabis investment space. Emily gives an inside look at how smaller companies can approach potential investors, and how she feels megastores will impact the industry.

When people learn the benefits of CBD 💚🌿💚🌿. For clarity in this article we believe the 👑 is referring to Hemp derived CBD not Cannabis CBD. Whether it's Hemp or Cannabis (Marijuana) CBD they both have healing medicinal properties which have been helping generations of people. 
Thank you Queen for sharing your experience. It is so important people speak out on the benefits of CBD.

Excerpt from the September 2021 issue of
@harpersbazaarus interview with @beyonce 
"During quarantine, I went from overindulgences to creating positive rituals drawing from past generations and putting my own spin on things. I discovered CBD on my last tour, and I’ve experienced its benefits for soreness and inflammation. It helped with my restless nights and the agitation that comes from not being able to fall asleep. I found healing properties in honey that benefit me and my children. And now I’m building a hemp and a honey farm. I’ve even got hives on my roof! And I’m so happy that my daughters will have the example of those rituals from me. One of my most satisfying moments as a mom is when I found Blue one day soaking in the bath with her eyes closed, using blends I created and taking time for herself to decompress and be at peace. I have so much to share…and there’s more to come soon!"
